    "short_description": "Craft beer, antiques, board games, and world-class art in OP's eclectic core.",
    "long_description": "Overland Park's downtown and Metcalf corridor offer a surprisingly diverse mix of destinations spread across a few miles of the city's older core. The Marty Street area anchors the northern end with a genuine neighborhood feel: Brew Lab is a beloved local craft brewery and kitchen, Petersons Antiques is a well-regarded shop that's been a fixture for decades, and Atomic Cowboy brings Denver Biscuit Co. and Fat Sully's NY Pizza under one roof for an all-day food and bar destination. A short drive south on Metcalf leads to Cardboard Corner Cafe, a highly rated board game cafe perfect for a laid-back afternoon. Nearby, the Johnson County Arts and Heritage Center offers rotating exhibits and permanent collections celebrating the region's history and creative culture — and it's free. For serious contemporary art, the Nerman Museum of Contemporary Art on the Johnson County Community College campus is a genuine gem, housing one of the most significant collections in the region in a striking building with free admission.",
